[panting heavily]

235
00:13:34,481 --> 00:13:35,482
What?

236
00:13:35,566 --> 00:13:37,150
Have you looked in the mirror?

237
00:13:38,026 --> 00:13:39,569
Who's gonna get out of the van?

238
00:13:39,653 --> 00:13:42,280
[panting heavily]

239
00:13:42,364 --> 00:13:44,449
Ah, fuck it. Fuck it.

240
00:13:44,533 --> 00:13:47,035
[stifled grunting, crying]

241
00:13:48,579 --> 00:13:50,038
He is.

242
00:13:50,122 --> 00:13:51,748
[chuckles]

243
00:13:52,833 --> 00:13:57,462
Got him. Like a rat in a trap
that I will kill with a hammer. [Chuckles]

244
00:13:57,546 --> 00:14:00,131
"Triple-D Car Hire." Leeds address.

245
00:14:00,215 --> 00:14:01,466
Registration number?

246
00:14:01,550 --> 00:14:02,926
[newscast plays indistinctly]

247
00:14:03,010 --> 00:14:04,094
That will take a while.

248
00:14:04,178 --> 00:14:05,554
[sighs]

249
00:14:07,264 --> 00:14:08,849
[Roddy] Get me a coffee.

250
00:14:12,352 --> 00:14:13,895
I need fuel for this one.

251
00:14:13,979 --> 00:14:26,825
An SQL injection attack will take hours, which leaves a malware bomb as the most effective method, but that needs someone to open an email, so… Cheers, Standish. Double espresso.

252
00:14:32,748 --> 00:14:34,249
[mumbles]

253
00:14:37,920 --> 00:14:40,046
[Louisa]
I thought you could hack anything.

254
00:14:40,130 --> 00:14:41,548
I can.

255
00:14:41,632 --> 00:14:44,342
I'm not saying I can't do it.
Just that it will take some time.

256
00:14:44,426 --> 00:14:45,844
How much time do you need, Ho?

257
00:14:45,928 --> 00:14:48,805
Because the kid's gonna get beheaded
in about, oh, two and a half hours.

258
00:14:50,432 --> 00:14:52,684
I'll tell you what I can do real quick.

259
00:14:52,768 --> 00:14:56,104
Check your search history
and tell everyone what porn you look at.

260
00:14:56,188 --> 00:14:57,689
Fine, 'cause I've got nothing to hide.

261
00:14:57,773 --> 00:15:03,611
- [scoffs, chuckles]
- [typing] - Don't you fucking dare. - [chuckles] Hey.

262
00:15:03,695 --> 00:15:06,281
- Stop it. Stop it. Stop it.
- What's wrong with you?

263
00:15:06,365 --> 00:15:10,201
- You're eight years old.
- [mumbles] - [Louisa] Pardon? - Where's my coffee?

264
00:15:10,285 --> 00:15:13,413
I didn't get you a coffee.
I got you the registration number.

265
00:15:13,497 --> 00:15:15,165
DE15 CGK.

266
00:15:15,249 --> 00:15:17,041
- [Roddy] What? How?
- Well, I rang them up.

267
00:15:17,125 --> 00:15:20,128
And said what? "Do you mind breaking
multiple data protection laws?"

268
00:15:20,212 --> 00:15:29,638
No, I said th-that I'd had an accident
with one of their vehicles and I had the driver's name, but because I was so shaken, I couldn't read the registration number I'd written down.

269
00:15:30,889 --> 00:15:36,103
I think the words you're looking for, Ho,
and these would be a first for you, are, "Well done" and "Thank you."

270
00:15:37,312 --> 00:15:39,689
It's on the list of vehicles
the Park are looking for.

271
00:15:39,773 --> 00:15:41,983
Then we need to get them
to focus on that vehicle.

272
00:15:42,067 --> 00:15:43,943
How do we let the Park know
that without them tracking us?

273
00:15:44,027 --> 00:15:46,279
Oh, my God. Min, a kid's life is at stake.

274
00:15:46,363 --> 00:15:49,241
I know, but Lamb...
Lamb told us not to get caught.

275
00:15:50,450 --> 00:15:51,994
Can't we track it ourselves?

276
00:15:53,704 --> 00:15:54,705
[sighs]

277
00:15:56,415 --> 00:15:57,415
[sighs]

278
00:15:57,499 --> 00:16:11,304
["I'm Gonna Be (500 Miles)"
playing on stereo] - [Dog 1] Oi! Stop! - [Dog 2] Stop!

279
00:16:11,388 --> 00:16:14,766
- [Dog 1] Stop!
- [indistinct chatter] - [indistinct radio chatter] - [Dog 1] Stop!

280
00:16:14,850 --> 00:16:17,019
[Dog 2] Stay in the vehicle.

281
00:16:19,104 --> 00:16:23,274
[mouthing lyrics]
♪ Yes, I know I'm gonna be ♪ ♪ I'm gonna be the man Who's working hard for you ♪

282
00:16:23,358 --> 00:16:24,609
[shouting continues]

283
00:16:24,693 --> 00:16:27,320
♪ And when the money ♪ [Dog 1] Stay there.

284
00:16:27,404 --> 00:16:30,156
♪ Comes in for the work I do
I'll pass almost every penny on to you ♪

285
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:32,242
[loud beeping]

286
00:16:32,326 --> 00:16:34,911
- [Dog 3] Move! Move!
- [Dog 4] Come on, let's go!

287
00:16:34,995 --> 00:16:37,247
- [shouting indistinctly]
- [Dog 3] Move!

288
00:16:37,331 --> 00:16:54,389
- [Dog 3] Go. Go. Go. Move.
- [beeping continues, stops] [mouthing lyrics] ♪ Well, I know I'm gonna be ♪ ♪ I'm gonna be the man Who's growing old with you ♪ ♪ But I would walk 500 miles ♪ - ♪ And I would walk 500 more ♪ - [tapping]

289
00:16:54,473 --> 00:16:57,308
[song continues on stereo]

290
00:16:57,392 --> 00:16:59,561
Can you get out of the vehicle, please,
Mr. Lamb?

291
00:17:00,270 --> 00:17:02,313
No, no, no. I'm quite comfortable
where I am.

292
00:17:02,397 --> 00:17:05,858
These seats are lovely.
And they're heated too.

293
00:17:05,943 --> 00:17:09,279
- Step out of the vehicle now.
- Nah, I'm... I'm... I'm okay where I am.

294
00:17:09,363 --> 00:17:15,536
You go fetch your boss and tell him
I've brought the car back, but we need to go over the damage waiver.

295
00:17:22,125 --> 00:17:27,214
You help us get petrol,
you help us get to the boat, and we will let you go. I swear.

296
00:17:28,924 --> 00:17:31,092
Yeah? Okay.

297
00:17:31,176 --> 00:17:36,806
- Listen, be cool. Okay?
- [coughing] [Curly] He's seen all our faces, man. He has got to go.

298
00:17:36,890 --> 00:17:40,185
No! Listen.
Why aren't you taking me seriously?

299
00:17:40,269 --> 00:17:42,020
'Cause I'm the one with the fucking gun,
remember?

300
00:17:42,104 --> 00:17:44,731
He's got a point. Look,
I don't like it either, but he's right.

301
00:17:44,815 --> 00:17:50,445
Please, please.
I'll say I never saw your faces or I never heard your voices or I blanked it out from stress.

302
00:17:50,529 --> 00:17:52,865
Oh, right now he'll say anything.

303
00:17:53,574 --> 00:17:55,241
My uncle's got money.

304
00:17:55,325 --> 00:17:56,451
Proving my point.

305
00:17:56,535 --> 00:17:58,286
No, straight up. My uncle's rich.

306
00:17:58,370 --> 00:18:01,873
Look, your exit plan, it... it might not
work, but my uncle, he can sort that.

307
00:18:01,957 --> 00:18:05,543
- He can help you. He can make something...
- You little fucking lying rat!

308
00:18:05,627 --> 00:18:08,005
Hey! Hey! Fucking stop it!

309
00:18:11,383 --> 00:18:12,968
- [pants]
- Your uncle.

310
00:18:13,802 --> 00:18:15,012
Where is he?

311
00:18:16,013 --> 00:18:17,014
Islamabad.

312
00:18:18,015 --> 00:18:19,182
Where?

313
00:18:19,266 --> 00:18:20,350
Pakistan.

314
00:18:20,434 --> 00:18:22,268
- [chuckles]
- What the fuck use is that to us?

315
00:18:22,352 --> 00:18:24,813
- You get your money and you disappear.
- This is such fucking bullshit.

316
00:18:24,897 --> 00:18:27,649
- He's messing with ya.
- Fucking stop it. I'm thinking, okay?

317
00:18:27,733 --> 00:18:29,943
- That should take a while.
- [laughs] Hey.

318
00:18:30,694 --> 00:18:33,488
[pants] Fucking don't. Okay? Don't.

319
00:18:33,572 --> 00:18:34,948
[breathing heavily]

320
00:18:40,329 --> 00:18:42,206
It's gotta be worth a shot, yeah.

321
00:18:43,498 --> 00:18:50,631
- Yeah?
- [scoffs] But you're coming on the boat too, and you stay with us till we get the money.

322
00:19:01,475 --> 00:19:16,156
- [song continues on stereo]
- [loud beeping] ♪ La la la, la la la La la la, la la la ♪ ♪ La la la, la la la ♪ - Get out of the car. - [continues singing] What?

323
00:19:16,240 --> 00:19:17,740
Get out of the car.

324
00:19:17,824 --> 00:19:19,826
[song continues on stereo]

325
00:19:19,910 --> 00:19:21,661
Is this a joke?

326
00:19:21,745 --> 00:19:23,538
No, it's the Proclaimers.

327
00:19:23,622 --> 00:19:31,671
- Get out of the...
- [stereo stops] Nick, relax. I brought the car back.

328
00:19:31,755 --> 00:19:33,298
You pulled a gun on me.

329
00:19:33,382 --> 00:19:37,844
Uh, no, I delegated that.
An... And any court of law will tell you there's a difference.

330
00:19:37,928 --> 00:19:41,556
And she didn't pull a gun on you.
She pulled a gun on... on your boy.

331
00:19:41,640 --> 00:19:43,684
Get out of the car.

332
00:19:45,602 --> 00:19:46,644
Are you gonna shoot me?

333
00:19:46,728 --> 00:19:49,773
- Not right now.
- Yeah, well, what about one of your lads?

334
00:19:49,857 --> 00:19:54,862
Hair triggers make natural
scratching posts for itchy indexes.

335
00:19:55,487 --> 00:19:57,071
They're not gonna do anything
unless you do.

336
00:19:57,155 --> 00:19:59,532
You got my word on that.
Now get out of the fucking car.

337
00:19:59,616 --> 00:20:00,784
All right. Good.

338
00:20:01,994 --> 00:20:04,538
'Cause I was wanting a little word
with Lady Di.

339
00:20:07,291 --> 00:20:09,167
[weapons cocking]

340
00:20:09,251 --> 00:20:11,211
All right, ah. [Grunts]

341
00:20:11,295 --> 00:20:15,256
Just reaching for a peashooter.

342
00:20:15,340 --> 00:20:16,341
Here you go.

343
00:20:20,179 --> 00:20:21,346
Park it downstairs.

344
00:20:21,430 --> 00:20:23,265
I could... I could murder a coffee.

345
00:20:23,765 --> 00:20:25,809
What's the canteen like in this gaff?

346
00:20:25,893 --> 00:20:47,581
- [Lead Dog] Dogs en route. Stand by.
- [siren wailing] What's your plan then, big man?

347
00:20:49,041 --> 00:20:53,044
Hey, you get out. You fill up the van.

348
00:20:53,128 --> 00:20:54,671
Nod, nod, nod.

349
00:20:54,755 --> 00:20:58,883
You fill up the van,
and we all get the fuck out of here.

350
00:20:58,967 --> 00:21:01,220
Yes? [Breathes heavily]

351
00:21:02,471 --> 00:21:03,680
Oi.

352
00:21:04,973 --> 00:21:06,308
Give him some money.

353
00:21:08,435 --> 00:21:14,566
- How do you know he won't do a runner?
- [Zeppo breathes heavily] Hey, listen, kid. You've got... You've gotta come back.

354
00:21:14,650 --> 00:21:16,484
[Curly]
See that lady in the front filling up?

355
00:21:16,568 --> 00:21:18,320
The one with the two kids in the car?

356
00:21:19,404 --> 00:21:20,405
Hey!

357
00:21:21,240 --> 00:21:22,658
Do you see that woman?

358
00:21:26,912 --> 00:21:31,541
If you do anything wrong, I'll walk round to the back of the van, and I'll get my axe out.

359
00:21:31,625 --> 00:21:34,210
And I'll cut her kids' heads off
in front of her.

360
00:21:34,294 --> 00:21:36,797
Then I'll cut her head off, then yours.

361
00:21:37,381 --> 00:21:38,715
And you know I'll do that, right?

362
00:21:39,842 --> 00:21:41,093
[breathes shakily] Yeah.

363
00:21:52,479 --> 00:21:54,606
Hey, kid. Don't fuck this up.

364
00:22:03,323 --> 00:22:06,535
[breathing heavily]

365
00:22:09,162 --> 00:22:10,914
[cap clattering]

366
00:22:11,748 --> 00:22:12,916
[thud]

367
00:22:15,377 --> 00:22:16,545
Diesel, yeah?

368
00:22:18,630 --> 00:22:21,341
Knobhead. Keep your eye on him.

369
00:22:24,303 --> 00:22:26,179
[cap clattering]

370
00:22:26,263 --> 00:22:27,347
[pump whirring]

371
00:22:27,431 --> 00:22:30,266
[customer] Excuse me. Hello.

372
00:22:30,350 --> 00:22:33,353
- [Curly] Oh, for fuck's sake.
- [Zeppo] No, no, no.

373
00:22:33,437 --> 00:22:36,189
- Oh, fuck off.
- I... I'm sorry, I-I-I need your help. Uh...

374
00:22:36,273 --> 00:22:39,109
Can't get me, um... me petrol cap back on.

375
00:22:41,195 --> 00:22:43,155
Maybe the attendant can help.

376
00:22:44,740 --> 00:22:50,537
Oh, no. 'Cause he's stuck behind glass
and, you know… - What's she saying? - …the only way I can get… Fuck this.

377
00:22:50,621 --> 00:22:52,539
…I gotta get moving again soon. [Chuckles]

378
00:22:55,751 --> 00:23:03,300
But I'll, um… But I'll, um... No, I'll... I'm... I'll work it out.

379
00:23:04,009 --> 00:23:06,929
Hey, Mervin. Help the poor woman.

380
00:23:08,805 --> 00:23:10,307
Hey, look, I'm sorry about him.

381
00:23:11,433 --> 00:23:14,645
Think he'd be a lot happier.
He's getting married in seven days.

382
00:23:17,814 --> 00:23:19,441
It's a stag weekend.

383
00:23:20,108 --> 00:23:22,110
Oh. [Chuckling]

384
00:23:22,194 --> 00:23:23,987
Oh, God. Sorry.

385
00:23:24,071 --> 00:23:26,406
It's... It's just 'cause you, um...

386
00:23:26,490 --> 00:23:28,575
You know, you look like that, uh...

387
00:23:29,159 --> 00:23:31,661
You know, the... That... [stammers]

388
00:23:31,745 --> 00:23:34,414
- You know, the, um... The... The fell...
- Oh, yeah. Yeah, I know. The...

389
00:23:34,498 --> 00:23:37,584
- The Pakistani boy that was kidnapped.
- Yeah.

390
00:23:37,668 --> 00:23:39,210
Yeah, I get it.

391
00:23:39,294 --> 00:23:41,087
- Had it all bloody day.
- Oh. [Chuckles]

392
00:23:41,171 --> 00:23:43,571
But I suppose we all just look
the same to you people, right?

393
00:23:44,716 --> 00:23:47,844
No. No, I wasn't... I wasn't... I... It's
just 'cause... [stammers] I was thinking...

394
00:23:47,928 --> 00:23:50,180
Oh, hey, uh... I was just joking.

395
00:23:50,264 --> 00:23:52,057
- Oh. [Chuckles, groans]
- Yeah.

396
00:23:52,641 --> 00:23:53,767
Sorry.

397
00:23:53,851 --> 00:23:55,518
How about I look at that cap
for you, yeah?

398
00:23:55,602 --> 00:23:57,979
Yeah, that'd be, um... Yeah, thank you.

399
00:23:58,063 --> 00:23:59,189
[sniffs]

400
00:24:06,154 --> 00:24:08,323
- [blows raspberry]
- Hey. Knock that off now.

401
00:24:09,324 --> 00:24:10,366
I'm sorry they're up.

402
00:24:10,450 --> 00:24:12,619
- It's all right. It's not your fault.
- [giggles] Nah, nah!

403
00:24:12,703 --> 00:24:14,996
Oh, that's really stuck in there,
isn't it? [Grunts]

404
00:24:15,080 --> 00:24:16,372
There you go. [Sighs]

405
00:24:16,456 --> 00:24:18,958
- Hey, thank you. Have a good wedding.
- Huh?

406
00:24:19,042 --> 00:24:21,211
Oh. Yeah, thanks.

407
00:24:21,295 --> 00:24:24,380
Just gotta get through a weekend
with these miserable morons first.

408
00:24:24,464 --> 00:24:25,716
[chuckles]

409
00:24:38,562 --> 00:24:39,771
[pump whirring stops]

410
00:24:43,150 --> 00:24:44,610
[Larry] Go and pay the man.

411
00:24:50,824 --> 00:24:51,825
[sighs]

412
00:24:51,909 --> 00:24:53,827
[customer] Hey, thank you again, love.

413
00:24:56,705 --> 00:25:01,460
Hi… [speaks indistinctly] She's leaving.

414
00:25:02,377 --> 00:25:04,017
There's nothing to stop him from running.

415
00:25:16,391 --> 00:25:19,228
Shit. Look at the TV.

416
00:25:22,105 --> 00:25:24,107
[breathes shakily] Um…

417
00:25:24,691 --> 00:25:25,943
[breathes shakily]

418
00:25:27,236 --> 00:25:28,528
Excuse me.

419
00:25:28,612 --> 00:25:30,572
Um… [breathes shakily] Um...

420
00:25:30,656 --> 00:25:32,407
For fuck's sake.

421
00:25:34,826 --> 00:25:36,036
Pump number?

422
00:25:41,208 --> 00:25:45,337
Uh… Pump number?

423
00:25:52,511 --> 00:25:53,720
Pump number one.

424
00:25:55,305 --> 00:25:57,140
[typing]

425
00:25:57,224 --> 00:25:59,226
[attendant] It's 94.60.

426
00:26:07,818 --> 00:26:09,319
Keep the change.

427
00:26:09,403 --> 00:26:10,653
Really?

428
00:26:10,737 --> 00:26:11,864
Thanks, buddy. [Chuckles]

429
00:26:19,705 --> 00:26:21,415
Go on. Go on, get in.

430
00:26:25,752 --> 00:26:27,004
[Larry sighs] Shut the door.

431
00:26:28,839 --> 00:26:31,008
- [sighing]
- [chuckles] Good job, kid.

432
00:26:31,884 --> 00:26:33,844
- Good job.
- [Larry] Did you get any change?

433
00:26:35,262 --> 00:26:36,471
I gave him a tip.

434
00:26:49,776 --> 00:26:51,778
Thank you, Nick. You can leave us now.

435
00:26:56,658 --> 00:26:59,452
- Three sugars. There's a love.
- [door beeps]

436
00:26:59,536 --> 00:27:00,746
[sniffs]

437
00:27:02,372 --> 00:27:04,374
Alan Black's body's been found.

438
00:27:05,709 --> 00:27:08,211
Alan Black? [Grunts]

439
00:27:08,295 --> 00:27:09,921
Ah, it rings a bell.

440
00:27:10,005 --> 00:27:12,674
[Diana] Ex-Slow Horse. Your man.

441
00:27:12,758 --> 00:27:15,302
Clearly involved
in the kidnapping of Hassan Ahmed.

442
00:27:16,428 --> 00:27:26,729
But you see, I remember a conversation
we had on a bench earlier this evening, where you told me you had a guy on the inside who had set the whole thing up. So not my man.

443
00:27:26,813 --> 00:27:32,652
I have a statement from someone
who saw you and Black meeting after he'd left Slough House.

444
00:27:32,736 --> 00:27:35,530
Struan Loy? Bless.

445
00:27:35,614 --> 00:27:38,241
You think his word stacks up against mine?

446
00:27:38,325 --> 00:27:40,201
There'll be others.

447
00:27:40,285 --> 00:27:41,786
Standish will show.

448
00:27:41,870 --> 00:27:44,289
And she'll turn when she knows
why you're at Slough House.

449
00:27:44,373 --> 00:27:49,336
- [Jackson sighs]
- And Moody, dead after committing murder himself.

450
00:27:53,215 --> 00:27:55,008
Oh, I'm sorry. I thought you knew.

451
00:27:56,760 --> 00:27:57,928
Sid Baker's gone.

452
00:28:06,603 --> 00:28:09,105
I'm gonna make you an offer, Jackson.

453
00:28:09,189 --> 00:28:10,732
[stammers] I'm sure. [Inhales sharply]

454
00:28:10,816 --> 00:28:15,820
I mean, obviously you have to have
this all wrapped up before Tearney lands, and I can blow the whistle on you.

455
00:28:15,904 --> 00:28:17,531
You don't have a whistle.

456
00:28:18,448 --> 00:28:20,992
All you have is a CV littered
with dead Joes.

457
00:28:21,076 --> 00:28:24,913
Well, I'm not sure your career
will survive the death of Hassan Ahmed.

458
00:28:24,997 --> 00:28:26,706
But anyway, make your pitch.

459
00:28:26,790 --> 00:28:30,001
I'm sure you've got some sweetener
to help me neck this absolute bullshit.

460
00:28:30,085 --> 00:28:33,880
Sign a statement that tallies with Loy's,
and that'll be the end of it.

461
00:28:33,964 --> 00:28:35,423
Oh, you mean the end of me.

462
00:28:35,507 --> 00:28:37,550
[Diana] You'd be fired, but no charges.

463
00:28:37,634 --> 00:28:40,470
And enough of a pension to keep you
in single malts.

464
00:28:41,054 --> 00:28:46,226
A heavily redacted file will state
that you were thinking out loud and Black went rogue.

465
00:28:46,310 --> 00:28:47,936
[stutters] When's Tearney get back?

466
00:28:48,020 --> 00:28:50,897
I mean, I would...
I'd love to run all this by her.

467
00:28:50,981 --> 00:29:03,493
Or we can sit here
and watch the Slow Horses walk in one by one and accept a job back here at the Park, while you fester in the basement until this is all cleared up, which I can make last a very long time.

468
00:29:03,577 --> 00:29:06,496
And if you get lonely,
I can always send Standish down.

469
00:29:08,123 --> 00:29:11,960
The treason charge against her
will be resurrected, and this time I can make it stick.

470
00:29:13,629 --> 00:29:15,088
[sighs]

471
00:29:16,840 --> 00:29:17,966
Oh.

472
00:29:19,051 --> 00:29:21,386
Oh, I think I might have been bitten
at the canal.

473
00:29:21,470 --> 00:29:23,304
[sniffs, inhales deeply]

474
00:29:23,388 --> 00:29:24,389
Oh.

475
00:29:25,474 --> 00:29:27,851
Well, it sounds like a wonderful deal.

476
00:29:28,477 --> 00:29:29,770
And hats off to you.

477
00:29:31,230 --> 00:29:33,649
You really got me boxed in. [Sighs]

478
00:29:34,983 --> 00:29:37,653
So print off a statement. Give me a pen.
[stammers]

479
00:29:38,278 --> 00:29:39,655
Fuck, I've just remembered.

480
00:29:40,656 --> 00:29:44,618
Yeah, uh, there... there was
something I meant to tell you as soon as I walked in.

481
00:29:45,619 --> 00:29:48,580
[clicks tongue]
The car that... that I returned.

482
00:29:48,664 --> 00:29:50,874
The one that's now parked in the basement.

483
00:29:51,792 --> 00:29:53,377
It's got a bomb in the boot.

484
00:30:04,012 --> 00:30:09,393
- [sighs]
- [door beeps open] - ♪ But I would walk 500 miles ♪ - [Diana] Duffy.

485
00:30:19,027 --> 00:30:20,362
[car alarm chirps]

486
00:30:28,453 --> 00:30:30,956
[whirring]

487
00:30:32,040 --> 00:30:34,292
[trilling]

488
00:30:34,376 --> 00:30:36,587
[whirring continues]

489
00:30:38,505 --> 00:30:51,768
- Fuck's sake.
- [door buzzes] [sighs] Fucking Lamb.

490
00:30:52,311 --> 00:30:53,562
What's he playing at?

491
00:30:57,941 --> 00:31:00,068
[sighs] Shit. Secure the building!

492
00:31:00,152 --> 00:31:02,696
Search it floor by floor!
We've got an intruder!

493
00:31:04,072 --> 00:31:05,407
Door!

494
00:31:21,131 --> 00:31:22,298
[door beeps]

495
00:31:22,382 --> 00:31:23,592
[sighs]

496
00:31:25,761 --> 00:31:27,804
[grunting]

497
00:31:29,181 --> 00:31:36,146
- [shushes]
- [breathing heavily] - Now, tell me where the file is, please. - Wh... What file? What are you even saying?

498
00:31:36,230 --> 00:31:37,605
Stop pissing around.
You know exactly what I mean.

499
00:31:37,689 --> 00:31:39,566
Whatever it is you think I have,
I... I don't.

500
00:31:39,650 --> 00:31:42,611
Can you just put that thing down,
then we can... [grunts]

501
00:31:43,362 --> 00:31:45,572
- Which one's the photograph in?
- What... What photograph?

502
00:31:45,656 --> 00:31:52,412
Taverner wanted me out
because she knew I took a photograph - of her and Alan Black. - I don't know what you're talking about, but she had plenty of reasons to want rid of you, mate.

503
00:31:52,496 --> 00:31:55,541
- Oh, you mean Stansted?
- Exactly. That's why you're out. [Grunts]

504
00:31:56,041 --> 00:32:00,462
I know what she did.
She got you to fuck me over at Stansted because she'd have an excuse to get rid of me.

505
00:32:00,546 --> 00:32:06,217
- It was your fiasco.
- [grunts] Now, I'm pretty sure that she'll have asked you to destroy that photograph.

506
00:32:06,301 --> 00:32:08,928
And I'm even more sure that
you'll have kept a copy for insurance.

507
00:32:09,012 --> 00:32:12,182
So tell me where they are, and then
I won't shoot you straight in the face.

508
00:32:12,266 --> 00:32:14,434
[breathes heavily]
Sorry, mate. You lost me.

509
00:32:14,518 --> 00:32:15,853
[both grunt]

510
00:32:18,313 --> 00:32:22,609
- Tell me where it is.
- [breathing heavily] - Hey! [Grunts] - [grunts]

511
00:32:22,693 --> 00:32:24,403
[chattering]

512
00:32:27,364 --> 00:32:28,782
Come on, come on, come on.

513
00:32:29,908 --> 00:32:31,159
Black.

514
00:32:31,743 --> 00:32:35,789
Black, Black, Black,
Black, Black, Black, Black, Black.

515
00:32:39,126 --> 00:32:40,460
Come on. Come on.

516
00:32:43,505 --> 00:32:44,505
Come on.

517
00:32:45,090 --> 00:32:47,301
[shouting indistinctly]

518
00:32:53,515 --> 00:32:55,642
[shouting continues]

519
00:32:58,270 --> 00:32:59,270
No.

520
00:32:59,354 --> 00:33:00,814
[shouting]

521
00:33:06,403 --> 00:33:09,322
[on PA system] All teams. All teams.
Evacuate workstations.

522
00:33:09,406 --> 00:33:14,285
Please start approaching a secure area
with passes and ID.

523
00:33:14,369 --> 00:33:18,123
This is a 1470… - [Dog 1] Move! Move! - [Dog 2] Come on! Let's go!

524
00:33:18,207 --> 00:33:20,250
[Dog 3] All right, everybody out this way!

525
00:33:25,380 --> 00:33:26,507
[sighs]

526
00:33:29,009 --> 00:33:30,219
Stansted.

527
00:33:34,848 --> 00:33:37,016
- Move! Get out!
- Move! Move! Move! This way!

528
00:33:37,100 --> 00:33:38,560
- [groans]
- Move!

529
00:33:38,644 --> 00:33:43,732
Stansted. Stansted,
Stansted, Stansted, Stansted.

530
00:33:49,196 --> 00:33:55,202
Motherf... Fiasco.

531
00:33:57,204 --> 00:33:58,205
Yeah.

532
00:34:02,042 --> 00:34:03,042
- Clear.
- Move.

533
00:34:03,126 --> 00:34:04,335
[Dog 1] We're evacuating this area.

534
00:34:04,419 --> 00:34:05,628
Move!

535
00:34:05,712 --> 00:34:07,714
- [Dog 1] Move, move, move.
- [Dog 2] Out, out, out!

536
00:34:13,846 --> 00:34:15,889
- [Dog 1] Coming through!
- [Dog 2] Clear out!

537
00:34:15,973 --> 00:34:17,431
[shouting indistinctly]

538
00:34:17,516 --> 00:34:19,893
- [Dogs shouting indistinctly]
- Out of the way!

539
00:34:25,440 --> 00:34:27,525
[Dog 1] All clear! Out! Out!

540
00:34:27,609 --> 00:34:29,069
- [Dog 2] Move!
- [Dog 3] Move!

541
00:34:31,405 --> 00:34:33,532
Webb, we have a code 1470!

542
00:34:37,494 --> 00:34:38,495
[door clicks]

543
00:34:40,539 --> 00:34:43,458
- [Dog 2] Down!
- [Lead Dog] Down! On the floor.

544
00:34:43,542 --> 00:34:44,668
[Webb groans]

545
00:34:46,920 --> 00:34:49,838
[news reporter]…extremely worrying,
and added to the investigation…

546
00:34:49,922 --> 00:34:51,049
[door beeps open]

547
00:34:54,136 --> 00:34:55,762
This is yours, I believe.

548
00:34:57,931 --> 00:35:01,518
Oh, yeah. Must have forgot
to attach the bomb part.

549
00:35:04,396 --> 00:35:06,856
Duffy and his men are sweeping
the building as we speak.

550
00:35:06,940 --> 00:35:09,150
I assume it was Cartwright
you smuggled in.

551
00:35:09,234 --> 00:35:12,487
Nah, I thought it was helpful
to test your security.

552
00:35:12,571 --> 00:35:15,448
I've got bad news.
Your guys are not very good.

553
00:35:15,532 --> 00:35:17,034
[phone rings]

554
00:35:21,079 --> 00:35:23,165
Put him in the basement, next to Loy.

555
00:35:25,375 --> 00:35:27,460
[clicks tongue] You got the gist of that.

556
00:35:27,544 --> 00:35:32,799
Yeah. Well, if my guys
were as good as your guys… [scoffs] …they'd be your guys.

557
00:35:32,883 --> 00:35:36,803
Now that little interlude is over,
perhaps you'd like to sign this.

558
00:35:42,434 --> 00:35:44,602
Before I do that, I just got one question.

559
00:35:44,686 --> 00:35:47,231
Who the fuck have you just
sent to the basement?

560
00:35:47,856 --> 00:35:49,566
[breathes deeply] Ma'am.

561
00:35:50,567 --> 00:35:52,193
- [Jackson] Good?
- [River] Yeah.

562
00:35:52,277 --> 00:35:54,571
Oh, no. I wouldn't do that, ma'am.

563
00:35:55,614 --> 00:35:56,698
Fiasco.

564
00:36:00,202 --> 00:36:02,287
[River sighs, sniffs]

565
00:36:06,208 --> 00:36:09,836
In three seconds, I could have
a dozen guns pointed at your heads.

566
00:36:09,920 --> 00:36:11,505
Yeah, but you won't do that.

567
00:36:12,005 --> 00:36:14,591
Because you don't want anyone
to see these.

568
00:36:17,678 --> 00:36:18,679
Here, look.

569
00:36:19,555 --> 00:36:23,225
There's you, and there's Alan Black.

570
00:36:24,309 --> 00:36:27,563
Huh? Remember setting up the thing
you're accusing me of?

571
00:36:28,397 --> 00:36:36,989
Kidnapping Hassan Ahmed
in a false flag operation so you could rescue him, look good and score some points.

572
00:36:37,698 --> 00:36:41,451
You did tell me all that earlier,
but this is evidence.

573
00:36:42,202 --> 00:36:45,914
Yeah, I've put your name in.
If you'd just initial the changes.

574
00:36:45,998 --> 00:36:47,332
Sign at the bottom.

575
00:36:48,584 --> 00:36:51,086
I met with an ex-agent.
That means nothing.

576
00:36:51,170 --> 00:36:54,422
Oh, you won't mind if we, uh,
send this to Tearney then?

577
00:36:54,506 --> 00:36:57,217
- And everyone else at the Park.
- And Hobden, while we're at it.

578
00:36:57,301 --> 00:37:00,136
No, no. Hobden's a kook.
Send it to all the news desks.

579
00:37:00,220 --> 00:37:02,347
- News desks. [Mutters]
- What do you want?

580
00:37:02,431 --> 00:37:04,099
I want that kid found alive.

581
00:37:04,183 --> 00:37:05,308
And you think I don't?

582
00:37:05,392 --> 00:37:10,188
I think your attention's been split
between finding him and burning me.

583
00:37:10,272 --> 00:37:11,356
[gasps]

584
00:37:14,318 --> 00:37:18,363
There are three possible vehicles.
We have lost track of all of them.

585
00:37:18,447 --> 00:37:20,615
We are doing everything we can.

586
00:37:20,699 --> 00:37:22,367
There's something more you could do.

587
00:37:22,451 --> 00:37:23,827
Cartwright got Hobden's phone.

588
00:37:23,911 --> 00:37:27,539
It turns out there's a certain someone
he called when it all went to shit.

589
00:37:28,457 --> 00:37:31,793
Maybe you should pay that someone a visit.

590
00:37:40,761 --> 00:37:44,556
Hey, this deal with your uncle,
how much money we talking?

591
00:37:44,640 --> 00:37:46,892
[stammers] Well, name your price.

592
00:37:47,643 --> 00:37:49,185
What is he? A billionaire?

593
00:37:49,269 --> 00:37:53,148
No, he... he's got businesses
and... and lots of investments. Lots.

594
00:37:53,232 --> 00:37:56,109
Oh, yeah? Well, how come
he never helped you out before?

595
00:37:56,902 --> 00:37:59,279
You was living in a right shitheap
back in Leeds.

596
00:38:01,114 --> 00:38:04,242
He... He said he wanted me
to make my own way, like... like he did.

597
00:38:04,326 --> 00:38:06,870
[breathes shakily]
But he wouldn't want me hurt. [Stammers]

598
00:38:06,954 --> 00:38:08,121
He wouldn't want me hurt.

599
00:38:08,205 --> 00:38:10,123
Hey, listen. Listen, why would he lie?

600
00:38:10,958 --> 00:38:13,418
Like you said,
he better not be bullshitting.

601
00:38:13,502 --> 00:38:19,132
Because if there is no uncle
and there is no money, - we're gonna find out, you know? - The money will be there, I swear.

602
00:38:19,216 --> 00:38:22,343
- Okay? I promise it's there. My uncle...
- Yeah, all right, all right. All right!

603
00:38:22,427 --> 00:38:23,720
Jesus.

604
00:38:25,180 --> 00:38:26,974
Look, he did well at the petrol station.

605
00:38:27,558 --> 00:38:29,184
You did.

606
00:38:29,268 --> 00:38:31,436
[Curly] So I'll give him
the benefit of the doubt.

607
00:38:32,646 --> 00:38:34,064
He can come with us.

608
00:38:35,482 --> 00:38:39,236
But only if he makes me laugh.

609
00:38:43,699 --> 00:38:44,741
If he fucking what?

610
00:38:46,451 --> 00:38:48,579
He's a comedian, isn't he?

611
00:38:49,621 --> 00:38:53,125
Well, I say "comedian."
He's never had the balls to go on stage.

612
00:38:55,335 --> 00:38:56,628
[Curly] Come on, now!

613
00:38:56,712 --> 00:38:58,588
This is your big chance.
You wanna come with us, don't ya?

614
00:38:58,672 --> 00:39:01,132
- Roast us like on Comedy Central.
- Make us laugh.

615
00:39:01,216 --> 00:39:03,051
- [Curly] Go on!
- Um...

616
00:39:03,135 --> 00:39:13,478
- [Larry] Waiting.
- Okay, okay. Uh… Um… So you're the Sons of Albion, huh?

617
00:39:15,272 --> 00:39:18,942
Just a hunch, but is Albion married to his first cousin?

618
00:39:20,485 --> 00:39:21,778
That's just fucking rude.

619
00:39:21,862 --> 00:39:23,906
That's the point. It's insults.

620
00:39:25,657 --> 00:39:26,657
[Larry] Go on.

621
00:39:28,243 --> 00:39:29,620
"The Sons of Albion."

622
00:39:30,495 --> 00:39:34,541
Because "Unfuckable White Men
with Daddy Issues" doesn't quite fit on a neck tattoo, does it?

623
00:39:36,627 --> 00:39:37,628
Dear me.

624
00:39:39,713 --> 00:39:40,714
Oh.

625
00:39:41,840 --> 00:39:43,383
I guess you got what you wanted.

626
00:39:44,384 --> 00:39:45,552
A Muslim bombing.

627
00:39:46,595 --> 00:39:48,179
- [chuckles]
- [laughs]

628
00:39:48,263 --> 00:39:51,099
[imitates explosion sound]

629
00:39:51,183 --> 00:39:53,309
[Zeppo laughs] Now, that's good.

630
00:39:53,393 --> 00:39:55,646
That is good. More.

631
00:39:57,689 --> 00:40:05,864
The Sons of Albion: Saving Great Britain from the infidels Monday to Thursday, but can't resist a good curry on a Friday night.

632
00:40:05,948 --> 00:40:13,997
- [Larry laughs]
- [Zeppo laughs] - He's talking about us! [Laughs] - [laughing] You know... Uh, you know there's 1.8 billion Muslims in the world?

633
00:40:14,081 --> 00:40:15,457
- [Larry] Yeah?
- He's on a roll. [Laughs]

634
00:40:15,541 --> 00:40:21,296
- You're gonna need a bigger van, mate.
- [laughing] Hey, do him.

635
00:40:21,380 --> 00:40:22,213
Do him.

636
00:40:22,297 --> 00:40:23,465
- Go on. Go on.
- Look at him.

637
00:40:23,549 --> 00:40:25,216
If he was any more inbred,
he'd be a sandwich.

638
00:40:25,300 --> 00:40:26,593
[laughs]

639
00:40:26,677 --> 00:40:29,387
Another one! Another one!
This guy! Another one!

640
00:40:29,471 --> 00:40:34,058
And this one, he's so dumb,
he's got a note in his underpants: "Wipe arse. Use paper."

641
00:40:34,142 --> 00:40:37,270
- [Larry laughs]
- [laughing] Hey!

642
00:40:37,354 --> 00:40:38,772
[laughing continues]

643
00:40:38,856 --> 00:40:40,356
You're fucking funny!

644
00:40:40,440 --> 00:40:42,484
He's laughing now! He's laughing...

645
00:40:42,568 --> 00:40:47,155
- God! [Laughs]
- [laughing] He's laughing now? [Laughs] He's laughing!

646
00:40:47,239 --> 00:40:49,616
[laughs loudly]

647
00:40:49,700 --> 00:40:50,868
[tires screech]

648
00:40:51,577 --> 00:40:52,744
[Zeppo] Ah, fuck!

649
00:40:53,996 --> 00:40:56,415
- [gasps]
- [gasps]

650
00:40:58,792 --> 00:41:00,710
[exhales deeply]

651
00:41:00,794 --> 00:41:02,921
[Curly chuckles, exhales sharply]

652
00:41:04,131 --> 00:41:05,132
Whew!

653
00:41:06,091 --> 00:41:07,217
[exhales sharply]

654
00:41:07,301 --> 00:41:09,761
Now that's fucking funny.
[inhales sharply]

655
00:41:09,845 --> 00:41:11,889
"Strange Game" playing...
